public class ClusterDisableServerRequest
extends AbstractRequest

Disable a cluster member. This process may be asynchronous if Session Clustering is used â€“ if this is the case, the initial operation will return an HTTP 202 response. As long as the server is not fully disabled, further calls to this method should be idempotent. On a ZSCM with no valid license, this operation will fail.
